cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with deep learning architectures for image classification and annotation, which are typically covered by the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of kernel machines and the focus on learning context-aware similarity functions suggest a strong connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of deep networks and the regularization term suggest a possible connection to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
